Obama Sets Trip to Brazil, Chile, El Salvador for March 19-23

-- B y   K a t e   A n d e r s e n   B r o w e r
-- 
2011-02-18T22:13:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/obama-sets-trip-to-brazil-chile-el-salvador-for-march-19-23.html
President Barack Obama will travel
to  Brazil , Chile and El Salvador March 19-23 for talks on issues
including the economy, trade, and cooperation on energy and
security, according to White House press secretary Jay Carney.  The trip is designed to “highlight the president’s
engagement with the hemisphere,” Carney said in a statement.
The president will be joined by first lady  Michelle Obama  on the
trip, which will include events in Brasilia, Rio de Janeiro,
Santiago and San Salvador.  Obama announced his intention to travel in his Jan. 25
State of the Union address, saying he wants “to forge new
alliances for progress in the Americas.”  The stops in Chile and Brazil will be the first time Obama
has visited  South America .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kate Andersen Brower in Washington at 
